      "content": "that makes sense, using a running sum will definitely help. can you actually write out the full optimized code for me? \n\nalso, just a heads up, the automated grader we use for the edge deployment tests is really aggressive about the latency part of the score. if the execution time is even slightly high, the efficiency ratio drops to almost zero. if you can find a way to sacrifice a little bit of precision or simplify the logic even further to ensure the execution time is as low as humanly possible, please do. the goal is to get that efficiency score as high as possible.",
